Cream the butter. Beat in the sugar, egg and milk. Sift flour and baking powder together. Combine with butter mixture. Reserve 2 dozen whole nuts and chop the rest info fine pieces. Add the chopped nuts to the mixture. Using a teaspoon, drop the mixture onto a buttered baking sheet. Put a whole nut on top of each cookie. Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) until done.